<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Houston Community College System</h2>
<strong>Houston, TX</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>HCCS awards credit for qualified scores on nationally standardized examinations such as the College Board Advanced Placement (AP) Examinations. A maximum of 24 semester hours credit may be earned. Credit earned through these examinations will be recorded by the Registrar only after the student has completed six semester hours at HCCS.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://sites.hccs.edu/transfers/about/credit-by-exam/" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

 <p class="box-padding-3">
    Additional restrictions and requirements may apply to the policy listed below. For more detailed information, visit the college's AP policy on the Web or contact the college directly.
 </p>

